Am seeing the same problem. Tested on `3.0.11` and `3.0.24` and no luck resolving the problem.

Seems to be JS -> TS compilation problem. In `time.js` there is an additional constant `const setTimeout_original = setTimeout;` that is being used to hide direct dependency, while this is missing in TS. The following fix in `time.d.ts` seems to fix this compilation issue: 
```
declare const setTimeout_original: typeof setTimeout;
declare const setTimeout_safe: (done: any, ms: any, setTimeout?: typeof setTimeout_original, targetTime?: any) => () => void;
```

